    "id": "b1-u16-theory",
    "title": "Learn the rule",
    "shortTitle": "Theory",
    "displayMode": "swipeable_cards",
    "completionRule": {
      "type": "view_all_cards",
      "required": true
    },
    "cards": [
      {
        "id": "theory-card-1",
        "title": "Subject pronouns",
        "subtitle": "Subject pronouns",
        "cardType": "rule_card",
        "sections": [
          {
            "type": "bullet_list",
            "title": "Use",
            "items": [
              "A subject pronoun tells us who or what performs the action of the verb."
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "example_list",
            "title": "Example",
            "items": [
              [
                "Look at those children! **They** are playing football.",
                "Maria loves baking, and **she** makes the best cakes in town."
              ]
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "theory-card-2",
        "title": "Object pronouns",
        "subtitle": "Object pronouns",
        "cardType": "rule_card",
        "sections": [
          {
            "type": "bullet_list",
            "title": "Use",
            "items": [
              "As the object of a verb (receives the action): The teacher called **him** to the front.",
              "After prepositions: Could you send the documents to **us** by Friday?"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "theory-card-3",
        "title": "Possessive determiners",
        "subtitle": "Possessive determiners",
        "cardType": "rule_card",
        "sections": [
          {
            "type": "bullet_list",
            "title": "Use",
            "items": [
              "To indicate who something belongs to. They always come before a noun: I left **my** keys on the table."
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "chips",
            "title": "Useful notes",
            "items": [
              "✓ Have you seen **our** new car?"
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "remember_box",
            "title": "Be careful",
            "items": [
              "**its** and **it's** are completely different words.",
              "The cat licked **its** paw. (= the cat's paw — possessive determiner)",
              "**It's** a lovely day today. (= It is ... — contraction)"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "theory-card-4",
        "title": "Possessive pronouns",
        "subtitle": "Possessive pronouns",
        "cardType": "rule_card",
        "sections": [
          {
            "type": "bullet_list",
            "title": "Use",
            "items": [
              "To talk about ownership without repeating the noun: I forgot my umbrella. Can I borrow **yours**?"
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "chips",
            "title": "Useful notes",
            "items": [
              "✗ This is mines bag.",
              "✓ This bag is **mine**."
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "remember_box",
            "title": "Be careful",
            "items": [
              "There is no possessive pronoun for **it**."
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "theory-card-5",
        "title": "Reflexive pronouns",
        "subtitle": "Reflexive pronouns",
        "cardType": "rule_card",
        "sections": [
          {
            "type": "bullet_list",
            "title": "Use",
            "items": [
              "When the subject and the object of the verb are the same person or thing: She hurt **herself** while cycling.",
              "To add emphasis — to stress that someone did something without any help: We painted the whole house **ourselves**!"
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
